{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, frameworks like UTDEBUG specifically fine-tune models to learn to generate failing unit tests for given buggy code, thereby directly serving automated debugging tasks [111].Future opportunities lie in developing deep, bidirectional integration frameworks.",
    "One promising integration pattern is LLM-guided exploration, where LLMs serve as intelligent components to augment traditional tools.",
    "For example, when the coverage of SBST tools stalls, LLMs can be invoked to generate novel test cases, helping them escape local optima, as demonstrated by CodaMosa [83].",
    "Similarly, LLMs can act as solvers for complex path constraints that symbolic execution engines struggle to handle.",
    "Sym [72] proved the effectiveness of this technique by successfully solving 74 previously unsolvable cases."
  ]
}